  "chapter": {
    "number": 63,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "God’s Vengeance on the Nations"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who is this coming from Edom,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from Bozrah with crimson-stained garments?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Who is this robed in splendor,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "marching in the greatness of His strength?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“It is I, proclaiming vindication,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2737
          },
          {
            "text": "mighty to save.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why are Your clothes red,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and Your garments like one who treads the winepress?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“I have trodden the winepress alone,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and no one from the nations was with Me.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I trampled them in My anger",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and trod them down in My fury;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "their blood spattered My garments,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and all My clothes were stained.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the day of vengeance was in My heart,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the year of My redemption had come.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I looked, but there was no one to help;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I was appalled that no one assisted.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "So My arm brought Me salvation,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and My own wrath upheld Me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I trampled the nations in My anger;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in My wrath I made them drunk",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and poured out their blood on the ground.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "God’s Mercies Recalled"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will make known the LORD’s loving devotion",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and His praiseworthy acts,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "because of all that the LORD has done for us—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the many good things for the house of Israel",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "according to His great compassion and loving devotion.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For He said, “They are surely My people,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "sons who will not be disloyal.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "So He became their Savior.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In all their distress, He too was afflicted,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the Angel of His Presence",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2738
          },
          {
            "text": "saved them.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "In His love and compassion He redeemed them;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He lifted them up and carried them",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "all the days of old.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But they rebelled",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and grieved His Holy Spirit.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "So He turned and became their enemy,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and He Himself fought against them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then His people remembered the days of old,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the days of Moses.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Where is He who brought them through the sea",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with the shepherds of His flock?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Where is the One who set",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "His Holy Spirit among them,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "who sent His glorious arm",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to lead them by the right hand of Moses,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who divided the waters before them",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to gain for Himself everlasting renown,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "who led them through the depths",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a horse in the wilderness,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "so that they did not stumble?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Like cattle going down to the valley,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the Spirit of the LORD gave them rest.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You led Your people this way",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to make for Yourself a glorious name.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Prayer for Mercy"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Look down from heaven and see,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from Your holy and glorious habitation.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Where are Your zeal and might?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Your yearning and compassion for me are restrained.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Yet You are our Father,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "though Abraham does not know us",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and Israel does not acknowledge us.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You, O LORD, are our Father;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "our Redeemer from Everlasting is Your name.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why, O LORD, do You make us stray from Your ways",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and harden our hearts from fearing You?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Return, for the sake of Your servants,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the tribes of Your heritage.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For a short while Your people possessed Your holy place,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but our enemies have trampled Your sanctuary.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "We have become like those You never ruled,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like those not called by Your name.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
